entries.title: Spain Arrests Suspected Letter-Bomber
entries.description: The 74-year-old man is alleged to have sent letter bombs to Spanish government leaders, U.S. and Ukrainian embassies and other targets.

entries.title: White House Approves Sending Abrams Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: The White House formally announced plans to deliver 31 M1 Abrams tanks, in a coordinated move in which Germany and other European nations will send their own tanks.

entries.title: Ukraine Repels Russian Forces in East
entries.description: Ukrainian forces repelled Russian attempts to advance in the country’s east, the country’s military said, while air-raid sirens across the country raised fears of possible Russian missile attacks.

entries.title: Bank of Canada Raises Rates, Declares Pause to Assess Economic Impact
entries.description: Canada’s main interest rate was increased by a quarter point to 4.50%, the highest level in over 15 years.

entries.title: In China, Young Women Become Accidental Symbols of Defiance
entries.description: A new generation of novice dissidents—many artists and writers—arrested after demonstrations against pandemic lockdowns is fueled by anger over a clampdown on freedoms and attacks on women’s rights.

entries.title: Pope Francis Says Criminalizing Homosexuality Is Wrong
entries.description: The pontiff said the church should work for the repeal of laws punishing homosexuality, the latest in a series of conciliatory gestures by him toward gay people.

entries.title: Swiss Court Finds Prominent Antiquities Dealer Guilty of Using Forged Documents
entries.description: Ali Aboutaam was given an 18-month suspended jail sentence and ordered to pay legal costs after he entered a plea bargain with the court.
